Getting Started

Setting up R packages

To start with, ggstatsplot and tidyverse packages will be launched using libarary().

packages = c('ggstatsplot', 'tidyverse')
for (p in packages){
  if(!require(p, character.only = T)){
    install.packages(p)
  }
}

Importing data

exam <- read_csv("data/Exam_data.csv")

Working with ggstatsplot

ANOVA Test

set.seed(1234)

ggbetweenstats(
  data=exam,
  x=RACE,
  y=ENGLISH,
  type = "bayes"
  
)
